Package: unimirt
Title: Applications of unidimensional IRT using the R package mirt
Version: 0.0.3
Authors@R: person("Tom", "Benton", email = "benton.t@cambridgeassessment.org.uk", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: This package is designed to make fitting unidimensional models using the R packahe mirt easy. More importantly it includes shiny add-ons to help with viewing the results of IRT analyses easier as well an app that facilitates item selection based upon IRT results. Finally it includes functions to make IRT linking of data sets that have been calibrated separately as easy as possible.
Depends: R (>= 3.2.2), mirt, shiny, ggplot2
Imports: dplyr, reshape2, ompr, ompr.roi, ROI.plugin.lpsolve, ROI, stats
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 6.1.1
